caption: We were desperate for a dinner spot that didn’t require reservations. We stumbled across this alley way restaurant. Great, even if you’re not vegetarian. We had pickled veggies, shrimp, beet salad. We had an issue with one of the entrees and the customer service was outstanding.
Beautiful location! Food was amazing too. Nice to have places that clearly mention vegan/vegetarian on the menu.

Thoroughly enjoyed their food and the location was about as cool as it gets.  We ordered a few small vegetarian sides and had a couple of beers.  Food was delicious and the ambience was great! Highly recommend.
Awesome food combined with awesome service. Must visit if you are a vegetarian!
Food here was great!  Service is good! Sitting outside in the alley makes it feels like old times New Orleans.
Had rolled uttapam and mezze plate, tasted like Heaven! Kudos to the chef for such a creative innovation! Will come back to try more Chef’s recipe! Needless to say server was also super nice!
Just such a fantastic hidden gem. I get their Mimosa Honey Biscuits every time without fail, they're EXCEPTIONAL. A great local restaurant you should absolutely support.
Great vegetarian and vegan food.

Vegans rejoice!!! Delicious food in the French Quarter, and open late to boot! I went twice in one week while I had guests in town... once, after taking my buddies out to dinner at a restaurant with no vegan options on the menu, I called to place an order on the way home. They were just about to close but took my order anyway. Kale Pesto pasta was SO delicious my omnivore friends asked me to take them there for dinner the next day! All of us found something on the menu and really enjoyed it. Thanks SO much, Green Goddess. You’ve got a loyal customer in me!
Greatest food on planet earth!
Unique food options in a cozy area. Do yourself a favor and try their house made Bloody Mary.
Amazing food! Cool vibes! Awesomer server!
Tummy seasonal salad and Indian food all vegan and gf

I love how their menu offers plant-based options. I tried the pecan orange mushroom pate and the vegan queso croquettas. Both were delicious! I also appreciate that they close at 10 pm so you can grab a late dinner or just a quick bite when you're hungry.
Wow! We had a wonderful lunch. Rolled uttapam, mushroom pate, gouda grits. BTW, the coconut and kimchi slaw on the uttapam is 🔥 !!

I was exited to go and try this place, but food wasn't the best. I had a well reviewed salad that needed up been just bunch of green leafs and some nuts on it... I added shrimps to it for protein, and they place 4 of them. My guest had a main dish Indian style which she said it was good. Overall service was good. If we want to keep businesses going through the difficult times, we better make a meal worth the trip. Also, it will be helpful if the city will lower parking rates downtown NOLA to promote people going there.

Lovely place. Great service. They are being very careful with covid so no menus when we visited. You need to look up the menu on your phone. Which I think is a great idea, only outside seating too. We had a vegan in our party and she was delighted with what was on offer.

We ordered the beet hummus and the mushroom pate' for starters. They were delicious and something we have never had before. For entrees, my husband and his friend ordered the duck sausage poboy, I ordered the tofu poboy because I had never tried tofu. It was very tasty with the sauce and vegetables on the poboy. I ate it all! My friend ordered the wedge salad which was absolutely delicious! The dressing was excellent! We really enjoyed sitting outside and catching up with friends we hadn't seen in forever. We will be back!😀
Ecclectic food choices all of which are amazing.
Was nice experience matched by excellent service.... Kale Salad and entree dishes were awesome~
Love it !!
Excellent food and service. Love this place.
A truly once in a lifetime experience. So many well developed and innovative vegan options. Not vegan, while they have other choices on the menu, trust me when I say you won't miss the meat.
Amazing experience! Service, food, drinks, and environment!
Got the DUCK SAUSAGE BREAKFAST PLATE & the ROLLED UTTAPAM! Love it!
Extremely rude service.
the service was very helpful and welcoming. feeling here is similar to a cafe in san jose i liked.
The Sticky Tofu is a great vegan option
It's so savory. Definitely worth a return visit.
Hot sauce
Not open but says they are
A hidden gem on Exchange Place - outdoor seating, great vegetarian and vegan options. If you're a carnivore, the Cuban sandwich is absolutely amazing.
Great service, amazing food, and a wonderful location. A great place to go to avoid a crown of tourist but still enjoy the great taste of New Orleans.
I inhaled the utta. So delicious. But the Bathroom was disgusting...
excellent food and cocktails! definitely off the beaten path and perfect for a romantic casual dinner with upscale fare.
Nice spot to go on a nice day. I believe they only have outside seating. Food was good, service was good.
Fantastic food and great service! The staff was awesome
We are from the Northwest and it was refreshing to find a healthy food restaurant.
Super good food
I would give it a 6 out of 5, if I could!
Very impressed.  This restaurant exceeded my expectations.  The food was delicious and well presented.

Located in a beautiful alleyway with lots of tasty selections for vegetarians and omnivores alike, we were Beyond excited to check out this place! However, we were devastated to have had by far the most rude, condescending, and passive aggressive service I've ever had at a restaurant.  We dined on the afternoon of Sunday, February 22nd.  Were it not in the thick of the Mardi Gras tourist season, I would have asked to speak with the manager, as our server was very rude to us, seemingly for bringing empty drink cups from tropical island, despite us ordering drinks from the restaurant. Ironically, only one of those drinks was served to us, because our server never seemed to care about us or treat anyone with respect. Outside of having the old empty drinks though, I wasn't sure why, because all of us we're very polite and cordial, complimenting the food only to be met with dirty looks. I guess it didn't matter to them because our party of six was enough for them to bake-in a 20% gratuity charge that we could not contest. I most certainly would not have tipped anything extra, and in fact would have demanded some of my money back, were it any other time of the year. A truly terrible representation of New Orleans service culture.  tl;dr - DO NOT GO HERE!!  Would give 0 Stars if possible for terrible and rude service, but the food and location is a 4 star experience at worst.

We were in town for vacation and this was the only place we could find with more than one or two vegan/vegetarian choices. We both loved everything, especially the patatas and mushrooms. Its a must stop for any vegetarian. They also have non-vegetarian entres that are superb.
I've had some amazing meals here over the years. I just wish they'd bring back / reinvent the sultan's nest dessert.
Low key, mellow. Solid cocktails, good food.
we had the falafel three tailed fish, and the Thai tofu. Both meals were amazing and packed with so many different flavors that mixed perfectly. Love this little hole in the wall!
Great food, but genuinely the worst service I have ever received at a restaurant. Would not go back even though it was tasty :/

Great service and the food is very tasty! We needed a place that had vegan and gluten free options and we're so glad that we found this place. They also have non-vegetarian options so it's great all around!
The vegan croquettas are great!

I was really looking forward to trying this place while visiting New Orleans.  My suggestion do not waste your time or $. There are much better options with much better service. Once we finally had the waiter come to our table, our server was so bewildered by literally any question  he was asked about drinks or the food on the  menu and just kept saying "I dont know" The food was bland at best, my mimosa was in a child size juice cup for $10 . After all this, the waiter than double charged my meal and when called out on it said "Dont worry this happens all the time" WHAT!?! (Still waiting for the pending charge of that to come off my account) We then asked for change for a $5  he gave us change for a $10, because we are honest people we corrected his obvious inability to count $ and gave him the difference which just made him more confused. It's really unfortunate! I was hoping.for better.
Amazing place. Good Vegan/Vegetarian options. Good friendly service.

Very mixed review of this restaurant I've been to before. Always good food, no question about that. However,  the service was fairly poor; service staff very unfriendly and seemed uninterested with work. This was my first time eating here with Celiac. The mushroom pate was listed as "gf", however when I asked if the bread was gluten free, the waitress told me it was not. How can the item be listed as "gf" but components of the dish have gluten? Very poor labeling so be careful!
Delicious!! Great vegan and gluten free options. Uttupam with shrimp was killer!
Uttupam was tasty, great break from heavy Creole food
Best salad in New Orleans, where fresh vegetables are hard to come by
Amazing food, this is where you wanna go if you're in NOLA and Vegan.
Great easily overlooked area in the French Quarter! Healthy, GF and vegan options as well food for the omnivores. Varied beer, wine and drinks selection. All outdoor seating.
Just here for a friend to get s bite to eat and she loved it
Some of the best food I've had in my life.. perfectly balanced flavours and menu items you wouldn't find anywhere else..
Food was great. Service was great.
One of our favorite meals on this trip, if not top. Spicy jam was memorable. Gluten free and vegan options easy to identify. Sweet potato soup 😋.
Go to place for vegans in NOLA the beet hummus is amazing! Food was fresh and looked as great as it tasted!
Great food options that are tasty but not so heavy. Nice ambiance in the alley. Service was friendly but took a while to get our meal, however it was very fresh.
The vegan lemongrass tofu sub was delicious. Fast and friendly service
Food was delicious! My only complaint would be the price. Very over priced for a tiny amount of food. Good experience overall though.

Good concept, poorly executed. Our table of five took up half the space because the table was so bulky. Biscuit and jam was very good. Sausage was cold, cheese was strangely melted, lots of things were chewy and overcooked. Grits were cold. Had to add salt to my dish because it had no flavor.
Vegetarian & vegan friendly, with no flavor compromise!
Biscuits were remarkably fluffy and delicious. Good vegetarian options.
Visit this spot when the weather is nice because the patio seating is one of the highlights.  They have a largely vegetarian menu that is flavorful and delicious.  Try the curry!
Best meat loaf I’ve ever had. Yummy salad. Great outdoor seating on cute side street.
Terrible service
The Thai tofu was really good, outdoor seating only but good atmosphere
For vegetarians this is heaven. We had tofu hash and burrata panini !! Simply delectable and worth a try !
Food is outstanding - fresh and delicious. Well done to the chefs. Service is rude and slow.
Food was amazing, service was prompt, just missed the fifth star because I can't remember at the moment.. I'll update later stand by.
Awesome, one of my favorite places in NOLA.
Great food, little pricey
Yummy, accommodating
Lovely creative, variety of foods.
Vegetarian escargot was exquisite!

Has potential but service is complete chaos. We showed up asking for a table inside for 4, and the guy who greeted us (no host) seemed bewildered we were there and said so and so should be happy to seat us, shouldnt she? To which so and so looks just as bewildered with a yes, I can? Good, great, that was awkward.  There was a table available, but 2 in our party had to share a bench and one side of the table, as the only other 4 seater table was taken by 2 people, one also on the bench and one at the only one of 3 chairs that intersected with our table (so we had to share our table with her back to us on one of 4 sides). There were seats at the bar that they wouldnt seat anyone in even though they were busy...why have them then?  There were 3 service people, all who waited on us at one point, no idea who our actual waiter/waitress was supposed to be. Everyone was running around like chickens with their heads cut off. The guy took our order and we waited. And watched our food sit for SEVERAL minutes getting cold, wondering who was supposed to bring it to us. I guess they were waiting for our 4th plate to come out with it, which it never did, because he forgot to put it in. So 3 of us got to eat our cold food as the guy said the 4th was "coming right out" for a whole 15 minutes because "the egg broke." It was obvious at a certain point it was completely forgotten, but why keep making us think it'll be out in a second when it'll clearly be another 15 minutes. Our one out of town guest had to sit hungry and wait while we all ate our cold food.  Our other out of town guest was a vegan, which why we chose this restaurant in the first place. She said her food tasted very fishy, and was definitely cooked in the same pan as fish. Not very vegan friendly after all.  For $60+ for 4 breakfasts with only water, I'd take my business elsewhere in the future.
Go here! The duck sausage plate and the boudin is outstanding. Friendly people. Lovely setting.
My daughter loved it.
I really enjoyed our visit, THANK YOU for VEGAN OPTIONS! Your location is perfect!

Recommended by a local couple as a great 'Veggie' restaurant.Visited last week, as previous reviews the food was excellent with a varied choice. Found the service friendly and efficient and the cost was also reasonable. Highly recommended if staying around The French Quarter. Paul & Brenda (UK).

Most rudest staff I have ever encountered. Absolutely floored with their lack of care, understanding or respect. If you have any allergies or intolerances towards hot/spicy food - DO NOT GO HERE. They don't even tell you the full ingredients on the menu. When you enquire or complain you receive 'Remember you're in New Orleans, you should get used to spicy food'. Yeah thanks for that. They were missing entire options on the cocktail menu. They didn't want to give us meals without certain ingredients my vegan pal couldn't eat. Everything is insanely overpriced - I paid over $40 for a tiny plate of potatoes with grated cheese and a plate of lettuce - couldn't eat the sausages because again, too spicy and they never said they were. To finish it all off, when I picked up my bag to leave, a GIANT COCKROACH RAN OUT FROM UNDER IT!!
I didn’t find the food here as good as other reviewers. Especially for the price. Although the staff is quite attentive.

Super tiny place with excellent food. We found this place when searching for vegan options for my husband. As a non vegan I love places that cater to both. We both had wonderful meals that are not your typical veggie burger and fries seen in typical vegan offerings. I had the sausage platter and biscuits with pepper jelly, he had the pickled plate and the falafel. We shared a vegan bananas foster for desert- it was awesome! The cocktails were creative and wonderful.
Awesome vegan options
Greasy food. Aweful customer service and a rushed atmosphere.

Terrible experience.  We showed up 20 minutes before the kitchen closed but they sat us which was nice. Food was great WINE was terrible and old.  Ordered a bottle and they came with an open one that was off.  I work in wine for over 16 years.  They said it’s because we did not like it.  The cork was bone dry and the smell was obviously oxidized. Tried another wine and it was good.  BUT they guy shows up with an already opened bottle that was not full and tries to pour it. It’s either a scam with their wines or they are just terrible. Very rude staff except for one bus boy.  Maybe we got them at an off night but I see a few really bad reviews so maybe not.  Food was great. But that’s all.

This is the second time I've visited Green Goddess, and I was really underwhelmed. I got a vegan mango pasta because it was highly recommended by two different wait staff. The pasta was okay but not worth the price. It was definitely way too heavy for the heat. Especially since they were only seating people outside. It's in a convenient spot, and I am glad they have vegan options. However I regret not going up the street to try Piscobar instead. If you're looking for fantastic food and atmosphere, I cannot recommend Carmo enough and suggest you go there instead of Green Goddess.
Good vegan and non vegan options. Good portions. Quality food and service.
Lovely quiet place off of Bourbon. I had the Watermelon Burrata Kale salad & Naked Mary.
Incredible vegetarian and omnivorous options in historic Exchange Place.
Loved the vegan options,  very tasty and well prepared .
Always amazing and guaranteed to provide delicious, unique, and healthy meals.
Very unique menu and something for everyone
Good ambience.. food is okay..

I really enjoyed the drinks here and the food was delicious as well. Well spiced and well balanced flavors. I enjoyed a duck pasta that had a lovely mix of flavors and textures. Their vegetarian offerings are phenomenal as well. As an additional bonus, the outside seating is quite cute.

Tiny sidewalk café opposite an art gallery in a cobblestone alley behind the Monteleone Hotel.  Vegetarian, vegan, gluten free and choices for fish, duck and meat lovers! I had half a wedge salad without the bacon, and the Rolled Uttapam which was an inventive take on an Indian classic, the tamarind sauce spiced just right. Friendly staff, relaxed atmosphere.  I will be coming back for 3 or 4 of the other vegetarian choices that looked wonderful on the menu. Good value, clean bathrooms, takes CCs.

Yes it lives up to the hype. Set in a gorgeous historic alleyway, outdoor seating, delicious options including gluten free options, caters to all sorts of allergies and sensitivities, inventive menu, attentive wait staff, I would eat here every day if I could.

My salad was great! Service was slightly out of sorts but not intolerable. One thing to note, they do not split checks, the bluntness about it is almost rude. It's 2019 people, get with the times. For that,, 3 stars. Unacceptable to not split checks in this day and age. What business wouldn't do as much as they can to make the customer's experience the best it can be?
Sometimes, in New Orleans, you just want a damn salad or something a bit healthier. This is where that opportunity exists.
It's a small place in an alley with outside seating. The food was unexpectedly good. It's a hippie kind of place so don't expect traditional. It's good and I would definitely come back.
Amazing place.  Great food and service.  Will visit again.
Good food but a little pricey...

I wish it was not still the case, but I am always amazed to find great vegan food. The green goddess puts all the heart and would of New Orleans in to its delicious menu. Great spot tucked away in an alley way with in the city. Lots of fun people watching to do while enjoying your meal.

Delicious, straight-forward, simple and cozy little restaurant. My girlfriend was pleased with how vegan & vegitarian-friendly this place is, in a city that certainly lacks this quality. Ordered food was brought out relatively quickly and prices were nice. Staff were laid back and easy-going. Definitely recommend this place for lunch.

My favorite spot in NOLA! This is in a perfect quiet little alley that is near everything. Make sure you bring some sunscreen, the best tables are outside and if you are pale like me you will want some sun protection. I would go on walking tours and then come here for lunch. It was a perfect way to break up a busy day of being a tourist, get a healthy lunch, and then not feel bad about getting that heavy gumbo or Cajun cuisine for dinner. This green goddess wedge salad is the best!
Hidden gem! Food is remarkable. Bright, vibrant colors. Hot and tasty food. Waters were kept filled by attentive wait staff. Did a dinner and lunch here within a couple of days, GREAT both times.
Excellent Bloody Marry and great food choices.
Cute little restaurant, but really great food! Had options for me and my meat eating husband and we were both extremely pleased with our food!

Very good food that focuses on healthy, farm fresh fusion menu. I recommend the Freekeh salad which is built around a roasted Mediterranian grain. Nice location in a French Quart alley with tables outside.
(Translated by Google) Very good food, very nice service, thank you  (Original) Sehr gutes essen, sehr netter Service, Danke

This was our favorite restaurant of all that we ate at in New Orleans. We had a group of six (three vegans — one who is gluten-free —, one vegetarian, and two who eat anything) and everyone was very, very happy with their meal. The staff was very fun, knowledgeable and helpful. When we got there there were no tables so we were going to carry the food elsewhere and they said no and brought a table out for us, and water for the dogs. We cannot wait to go back. The best thing was that we were there during Mardi Gras but when you get to this restaurant it feels so private and far away, you can’t even hear any of the noise of the party going on just a very short distance away, it was so relaxing.
Great fresh food and service.
Super cozy nook with tasty and refreshing vegan plates. Got the mezze plate and rolled uttapam😋
Great fresh food! Im vegan and i went there with my dad who is not, lots of options for both of us! we had the falafel sandwich and wedge salad with shrimp and both really enjoyed!
Loved the falafel sandwich
Expensive but delicious! Great vegan options!
Came up on google as a vegan option but the choices were very small. It was mostly meat which I found odd. It was very over priced for the portion & quality of food.
Great food and setting
Food was excellent. Recommend the hummus. Bohemian vibe, relaxing atmosphere and location. Wish the bathroom was in better repair.
Wonderful menu. Plenty of vegetarian choices
This place is amazing. Can't wait to go back
Wonderful food and very good service.
Delish juice and salad

Was really grossed out by how dirty our drinking glasses were... they must be having major dishwasher issues, but concerning that they’d actually serve customers with them. Food was OK, a little more conventional than described online, but decent. Grits were good, but the salad was just $$ spring mix. That drinking glass coated in dried dressing that was slowly being rehydrated by ice water was unappetizing. The slow, apathetic service was a little much, too. Maybe just an off day.

It was a little pricey, but I got the green goddess salad and special-requested their falafel on top. It was the PERFECT complement and should be made a regular option for their salads. I will remember that salad for a long time. Thanks!
Meh. Slow. Food was average. And one of our water glasses was very gross.  But if you _really_ want to have a meal in an alley in the French Quarter, don't let this review discourage you.
Nice food but you have to seat outside whatever the weather is....
Food was amazing. Atmosphere is great at night.

Really enjoyed it! The menu online isn’t as comprehensive as the one you get there so check it out. As a vegan visiting New Orleans, I wasn’t sure I’d have a ton of restaurant options but it was delicious. I got a vegan falafel plate and my friend got the lemongrass tofu po boy. Staff was friendly to us and food didn’t take long at all. (IG: @lawfullyvegan)

Went at 2:15 on a Sunday. Ordered our food and waited. And waited. And waited. An hour later, we checked in with the server. She said she would look into it. Food finally came out 15 minutes later, steaming hot. It was obvious they forgot our order. Only thing that saved this place from a 1 star review was the fact that the food was pretty good.
Good food, fun spot. Vegan options.  Skip the beet hummus, lacks flavor.
Delicious the staff not too freindly. Overall enjoyable with veg options.

Excellent service- friendly staff. Sweet location, outdoor seating and wonderful food- many delicious choices. Healthy great choices for vegetarian, vegan and omnivores! Awesome cocktail menu as well.
Nice alleyway to sit outside. Very healthy food. Good for leisurely lunch.

The food was ok, but not amazing. We got a soup, salad and the mushrooms entree. We were hungry so we finished everything from the plates :) but some flavors were really off. The kale in the salad was too salty. The rice and didn’t have much flavor, the plantain was actually good! But the rest was pretty much ok. It’s a nice place to find healthy food, and the outdoor seating is nice since it’s in the alley.
Lots of great options for vegan, veg and gluten free.  Delicious dressings and sauces.
Very good vegan fare.

I was originally going to order the étouffe but I ended up going with the cheese, tomato, and greens sandwich (forgot the name). The sandwich was very bland and had no real flavor to speak of, plus the service was just OK.

We got there and were told that a table would be free after 15 mins by the female server. Bartender was really nice and made our drinks while we waited. Once a table was free the bartender then told us to sit down at the table. However, the service went downhill from there, we were not given water for the table, utensils or a menu for a good 15-20 mins. We even tried to flag someone down but were completely ignored. Had even watched a couple get seated, served water, given a menu and looked like they even ordered their food before anyone gave us any attention. Finally, we had ordered dinner with a bottle of white wine. I could not help but feel disliked by the female waitress who served us the wine but waited a while before returning with the ice bucket till after we told our passing bartender that we were waiting for it. The waitress finally got us our ice bucket but set it on the table when we already had been running out of table space. I thought it was funny since she had given the table next to us an empty seat to hold their bucket when there were other empty seats available around us too. We ended up having to put it on the floor. Food arrived and it was good. However, once we had finished our meal the waitress came over with the check including 20% service charge. Again, I thought it was even more funny since she didn’t bother asking if we wanted dessert or anything else to drink but spent time with all the other tables other than ours. When asking to take off the included 20% tip we were given attitude by the male busboy and no one wanted to even talk to us afterwards, practically slamming the check on the table when she brought it back.  Left the restaurant not wanting to return and made sure we left some tip with our bartender because she was the only one who made any effort. For some reason, I can’t help feeling it was because I’m Asian as every table had been served soo much better than mine. We were given the explanation that it was due to the Jazz Fest event but very hard to believe when smiles/attention were everywhere but at our table.

The variety of food here is great for all sorts of needs, vegetarian and gluten free. Outdoor seating only was very nice. Unfortunately the service was lacking due to a server that made us feel like an inconvenience.
Good food. Great people in amazing setting.
Exquisite trinkets
Had the falafel crusted sheepshead and crawfish cakes, the specials of the day and I’m in love!!! Great vibes and great service
We didn't eat here this time because we had already eaten when we found this place. Will be back.

Didn’t even eat here because of the weird vibes. I don’t think it was employees, it seemed like it was coming from management, but customer service was a 0. Tried to get to go because they have such a small space and they were almost violently against it. Again, it seemed like the employees were stressed about it because of pressure from above, but just be ready to wait and have meh service if you want to eat here. I think they are riding on the high of being one of the only vegetarian restaurants in the quarter — but I don’t think that I should have to sacrifice service for food. Jeez.

What started off as a really promising lunch amongst friends turned into an afternoon of hell! The Lithuanian manager/server deserves a special mention as he made sure that any of the 8 of us will NOT ever be dining there again! Aggressive, condescending, patronizing and extremely unprofessional are just a few of the adjectives we can use to describe his behavior. We waited around 30min for a table on a Saturday afternoon which was no problem at all... once seated we waited around 30min for somebody to take our food order... we were not asked for other drinks and when eventually we managed to order more drinks they messed that up too. We waited around 1hour 20min for food and when asking how long food would take the Lithuanian chap suggested we walk to McDonald’s if we prefer... They automatically added a $60 tip onto our bill which was 20% of the bill but we felt this was totally unjustified because of the terrible service. We also asked before we ordered that the bill be split and that we were separate parties but upon completion of the bill they did not split it and then said we could only use a maximum of 5 credit cards which is no problem but was never mentioned at all in the beginning. What a shame as the food was great but service and people skills shocking and very embarrassing for a restaurant. We will not be coming back and suggesting that everybody avoid at all costs. The staff ended up finger pointing and asking us to leave. We did so gladly...
Was my go to lunch place. My last experience was a bit disheartening. The server was extremely rude.
The tofu dish was amazing. I want to go back and try some of the other vegan options. Wait staff good. Very busy, be prepared for a bit of a wait, but well worth it.
The crab cakes were divine.

Such amazing food!! For vegetarians, vegans or not!! So good we went twice in our 4 days in New Orleans! Sitting outside in the exchange place alleyway is lovely when weather permits! Shrimp and Grits cake was amazing!! Wedge salad and patatas not pictured but also amazing! The patatas I got twice and I'm still mouth watering over the flavor! Crawfish salad was a special and delicious.  Dessert Vegan banana foster and a BACON sundae (praline ice cream). Will go back next time I'm in NOLA for sure!!!
Great vegan and vegetarian place with innovative fusion food.

The flavors are amazingly out of this world. They have taken this simple uttapam from India and transformed it using local New Orleans flavor into something totally out of this world.  The seating is outside and the service is pleasant. A nice place to come for casual dining.
Excellent food! Uttapam was a very delicious twist on original dish, a must try.
Just plain rude! Most of the items on the online menu not available anymore! And when you call in the most disgusting people answer the phone!
Food and service were superb. Perfect for those with dietary restrictions
The service was wonderful and the food was very unique! It was different but I really liked it.

We enjoyed the tofu sandwich, mushroom pate and beet salad. The beet salad came with a pepper jelly vinaigrette, which was a great combo with the beet. We had a nice spot outside and the staff was great. We did come in at peak lunch time so it took a while to get our food.
Good, but a little overpriced
Excellent food!

So appearently this place doesn't like doing delivery, as I was advised my Door Dasher, though I'm not sure why they took the order in the first place? Tastes just okay but as you can see there was no love put in preparing or packing up these meals. 2 stars is a generous rating.
Delicious salads and wonderful service. I will be back for more!
Super friendly and the food was fresh and tasty!
Hidden jewel in new Orleans. Never gets disappointed on dishes here. If you are a vegetarian, this is the place you must stop by

Great little place tucked away in an alley. Initially went there so my vegan/vegetarian daughter could actually eat something, lol. But they had food for my wife and myself too. I had a Swedish meatball/meatloaf sandwich (great bread) and awesome sandwich! My wife had shrimp and grits, c’mon, don’t get much more New Orleans than that. (Well, maybe the fried chicken and red beans & rice I had at Monty’s. But that’s a whole other review 😉
Good quality food , a variety of vegan choices. Quiet location in the middle of a busy French Quarter. Only outdoor seating.
The food was tasty and a tad expensive. Had the falafel platter... the portion was huge!
Perfect location and ambience. Food was delicious and staff were really nice

This place only has outdoor seating I think, it feels very much like Europe with outdoor cafe style eating. And the food is super healthy and delicious! They have fresh juice too. Overall, very refreshing place for a bite after eating all kinds of fried (yet yummy) food throughout New Orleans. The quaint street it’s on and the blooming flower trees nearby aren’t too shabby either. Would highly recommend and will be visiting again.
So delicious
Sausages were awesome, service is all outside so when it rains, it's not fun. Servicers are a bit grungy, but friendly.
Delicious food with a diverse menu that services many dietary needs
Best veggie food in the city
A yummy stop. Interesting diverse menu. Keep on mind its an outdoor cafe so come when the weather is good! Service is good and quick!
For vegetarians who need a break from seafood - go to this place. Fresh, great tasting and well prepared food. I loved it!
Delicious!! We got the uttapam and patatas and they were so flavorful. And the bouncer looking guy was so cool explaining things and some gems of the town. Yummy vegetarian
Super cool restaurant.. i love it ! Food was delicious, waitress was nice.. I have just one - restroom.. it was disgusted.. :-(
Nice banana foster! Made vegan!
Oh my! The food is amazing. Even the coffee is some of the best around.

Absolutely one of the best experiences in New Orleans. Our waiter, Sam was perfection. His recommendations in wine, apps, and lunch were remarkable. Best waiter of our trip by far! Now let’s get to the food... holy WOW! Melt in your mouth greatness. Gazpacho with lump crab meat is a must. Finish it with the blue cheese and bacon salad. Don’t forget the Evolucio wine from Hungary. Beautiful little street this restaurant sits off of as well. Love this place!
Great vegan yummies and cocktails
Unbelievable flavor combinations. The freekah salad, damn....it is really amazing!
Try the Hongo. It's healthy and different. The place is tucked away in a cute alleyway
I love the fact that they have veggie items for New Orleans classics!
Delicious and big portions
Place is dope
Super over priced for vegan options and Portions are small at that too.
Uttapam is AMAZING!  It's an Indian pancake with delectable accoutrements.
Small place with amazing food. Many vegan options! Staff is friendly and helpful.
Excellent vegetarian food options. We had the Thai tofu and the uttapam and they were fantastic. Also try the patatas bravas and cheese grits.
Mezze was Ok. My girlfriend had a Rolled Uttapam and loved it. A ton of vegetarian/vegan options
Delicious, cozy,cute Nice atmosphere.  I had the biscuit egg grits and shrimp. It was very well done and was a good portion. I would definitely reccomend.

Wasn’t too impressed by the food, I had a falafel sandwich which was overly salty, my girlfriend had a panini that was too oily.  We got waited on by three people none of them smiled once to the degree that we thought there was something wrong, so we struck up a conversation with one of them (shaved head with big beard), he seemed fine just not much of a converser I guess. I’m not holding that against them but when all the staff seem cold and indifferent, customers will sure feel unwelcomed.
Yummy place,
Yummy veg! Thank you!! Awesome flavors Great people.
Neat little place nice if you can sit outside and eat, limited bar, good food just don't go inside
Gourmet southern food with flair. The prices are high, but the food is well worth it. We enjoyed the sausage plate and patatas bravas. Never had more delicious drinks and apps!

Food is SO GOOD, light, healthy and delicious. In a cute little nook of a location. The staff is nice. Definitely worth it. I had the tofu po boy, it was like a bahn mi sandwich. Salads are great and plenty.

(Translated by Google) A find! A great choice for healthy and delicious lunch! There are several salad options, sandwiches, natural juices and entrees. The service is great and has several vegetarian, vegan, gluten free options. The place is quite small, however it has tables outside. We ordered two salads: Beet Burrata Kale eNuts and Cherries. Both delicious and very well served! It gives 3 people to eat very well!  (Original) Um achado! Uma ótima opção para almoço saudável e delicioso! São várias opções de salada, sanduíches, sucos naturais e entradas. O atendimento é ótimo e tem várias opções vegetarianas, veganas, sem glúten. O lugar é bem pequeno, porém tem mesas na parte externa. Pedimos duas saladas: Beet Burrata Kale eNuts and Cherries. Ambas deliciosas e muito bem servidas! Dá para 3 pessoas comerem muito bem!
Go for the specials! A flavor adventure
Loved the small European vibe of Green Goddess. All the veggie options you could ask for and the Raclette was delicious. Service was fast and on point. Highly recommend!
Is all of America this expensive now ? . But the food was superb!
Very good restaurant. Me and wife loved this place and my wife is vegetarian  she liked the lemongrass sandwich

Not thrilled. The Naked Mary was grainy and tasteless, my son-in-law had the drink with scotch and said it was “peaty.” My French onion soup was overly sweet and nothing spectacular. We usually enjoy these out of the way places but this one didn’t work out. Turned out to be an expensive and not very good place to get appetizers and our waiter turned surly when he found we weren’t there for a full meal.
Finally, a place where a vegan/vegetarian can take everyone who eats non-ve food and everyone is happy. This food is fresh and delicious. The staff are great. Thank you for a fantastic experience.
Amazing food!! I had the drunken duck pasta and my fiance had a vegan and gluten free dish. Everything was incredible. Please go to this place. You will not regret.

I was very excited about this place, but I am sorry to say that it was bad, even terrible. Many things were wrong. We paid 11$ for a glass of red wine and we could tell the wine was old and not flavorful. Then, on the wedge salad, the cheese was the rind, tough and not appetizing. Then was the main dish. We got a special that was supposed to be gnocchi and it was NOT. It was mashed potatoes in spoonfuls and burned to hell?? The special was 18$?!?!?! This was the worse restaurant experience I've had in a long time. I will attach a picture if I can figure out how to.
Yum!
Yummy food, friendly staff, decent amount of vegan and veggie options. A bit expensive for my taste, but the food was quite good

Hands down the best curated menu in New Orleans! Being a vegetarian it’s a struggle to find veg food in the meat loving town of New Orleans. But green goddess is a must try. Their dishes are carefully chosen, from a variety of local dishes to a few Caribbean and an Indian dish, it’s just worth the $$$. Not to mention the house specials as well. A must try, hidden gem right in the heart of the French quarter. ❤️❤️❤️

Decided to go as my friend is vegan and it was listed as mixed options for me the meat eater.  We walk 15 to be told that Dinner starts at 5pm over an hour away and the wine menu and aperitif is all they had right now at 3:30ish.  They had about 10 tables set up in the alley way.  We never did eat here, but I bet the people watching us great.
Very interesting , different food. Not for everyones taste. Very laid back service, so if you are one of those "my server should shine me shoes" type of person- go elsewhere.
Amazing food! Friendly staff

Tiny restaurant with only outdoor seating, liquor, and not a large menu. I ordered the Redfish special and it was outstanding - perfectly cooked. Everyone else at my table was similarly impressed. For a moderately priced New Orleans restaurant you can't beat it. The eclectic menu includes both vegetarian and meat dishes so there's something for everyone.
Awesome restaurant in an alleyway!
I don't miss an opportunity to eat here when I am in the city!  Creative, delicious food that changes with the seasons, Green Goddess never disappoints!!  Love, love, love!!!
Amazing food great service

I’ve eaten at the GG a handful of times. It’s just a block away from my home in the Quarter. You can’t go wrong with the Biscuits & Gravie’s Shrimp Etouffee (attached photo). Everything on the menu is something to be treasured. This is definitely a great spot for a nice brunch. Keep in mind, only outdoor seating.
Omgosh the tofu vegan poboy is so delicious.

Stumbled on this last time we were in NO. Came back again because it is delicious, surprisingly good cocktails and the food is delicious, varies dishes and healthy! (not easy to find in NO)!  Great place!
Great, fresh, and unique food in a beautiful setting.  My favourite place in New Orleans!
Plenty of outdoor seating, and tasty food. I had the vegetable panini it was heavy on cheese but overall pretty good.
Amazing place amazing staff, the food feels good, u feel transported sitting there eating with that amazing outdoor space. Must eat here! Especially if you like food!
Excellent vegetarian dishes. Terrace is in a cozy alley. I recommend the picked beats and any of the salads.
Lovely little spot with great vegan fare. Big portions and only exterior seating.
Nice seating available outside for people watching. Good hummus that has beets in it. Delicious! Good rum "Old fashioned" cocktail. "RIGHT HOOK" cocktail shown in picture.

(Translated by Google) Great food. Those who are tired of English muffins and sandwiches should stop here. In the French Quarter on a side street "Exchange Place". Prices reasonable and service very hard-working with us Germans.  (Original) Tolles Essen. Wer English Muffins und Sandwiches leid ist, sollte hier einkehren. Im French Quarter in einer Seitenstraße "Exchange Place". Preise zivil und Bedienung sehr bemüht mit uns Deutschen.
I have eaten here before and it is great. The only problem is that they are closed. I can’t get out of them when they will open again but at least for the “summer” they are not open.

Visited NO during Labor Day weekend  & was pleasantly surprised that this place was literally a 2-minute walk from my hotel (Hotel Monteleone). During my stay, I had the beet hummus and assorted fresh vegetables and toasted bread (pic attached) from the starters offerings, the freekah salad, of course from the salad offerings, and the rolled uttapam (pic attached) and the local grilled lemongrass tofu poboy, both from the plates offerings. OMG, SO DELICIOUS!  The restaurant isn’t 100% vegan, but they have several vegan dishes and offer to make several of their other dishes vegan upon request. This is great, especially if you’re visiting with people who aren’t vegan, everyone can still eat together. Friendly staff! I highly recommend The Green Goddess!! I only gave it 4 stars because the inside of the restaurant is quite small, but they do have a few tables & chairs outside under large umbrellas, so that if it’s a nice day and you don’t mind eating outside, you can do that.

Great dinner experience. The area is charming, staff is fun and food is creative and delicious! I got the falafel since I'm vegan and my husband got the meatloaf. He loved his meal and said he could have eaten ten more servings!
Discovered this restaurant during our walking tour. Perfect for vegan!
I walked in and out ... smelled like grease
The food was delicious. Try the beet hummus. It was amazing!
Very small portions.
Outdoor seating in Nola summers is rough.  Menu is limited and quality of food is okay.  Really probably best for non adventurous  tourists.
Really good food, good service and strong cocktails
Really tasty food. Lots of options.

I love this vegetarian-friendly casual restaurant which is full of character, tucked away on a charming side street. The staff are great and the fusion salads are brimming with a galaxy of flavours and colours. There is mostly outdoors seating but they will let you eat at the bar if there are just one of two of you. It should be open 7 days a week though.

I was pretty excited to visit some local vegetarian spots, and had this one saved for when I was in NO again. However, one of the employees (owner/hostess?) was quite rude and somehow that makes the food just...okay. I certainly wouldn't recommend this place to anyone. I look forward to trying other restaurants in the area.
Delicious and nutritious! Had the citrus hongo. Highly recommend. And the location is super romantic. Came here alone, but would come back for a date. Not super pricey,  but not cheap.
Pricey vegetarian and vegan food. Not as good as the Seed of you want more vegetarian/vegan food.

It was hard to find a healthy and delicious option near where I was staying (Royal St. Charles Hotel), but I was so glad I was able to find this place within walking distance. I had an excellent dinner at this restaurant. The tables were located outside in a quiet alley that provided a comfortable, breezy place to eat. The staff was attentive and very patient while I sat down and waited for my party. The Indian-style dish I ordered was delicious. The kale salad was very colorful and tasty as well. The menu offered a variety of choices for different kinds of eaters, including vegetarian and vegan. We came here on a Sunday evening at around 5:30pm. There was no line. However, you should probably expect a line if you plan to eat on a Saturday evening. I highly recommend this restaurant.
Small,  quaint, par staff, poor communication.  They stay open, but dont serve food, just cheese plates during late afternoon /early evening ( @4:45 )

First of all there is only outdoor seating so if you like air conditiong this is not for you, second of all when you arrive you have no clue where to go or who to check in with, when you finally order the dishes listed have all of their ingredients (in fancy names) and listed as sides so when you order you excpect to recive a plate full of lavish food but when it comes its 2 loaf cakes of food. The service is exceptionally horrible the waiters are not worried about you never check on you and by the time they come to give you water its WARM. Even though the food is good it doesn't make up for the horrible atmosphere and service.
Delicious food and a lovely atmosphere—low key seating in a little side alley. The crab salad special was absolutely wonderful.

A little hide away joint serving up excellent fresh and healthy food. It can be hard to catch a break with all the heavy and often unhealthy food around. A tad expensive, but regardless I highly recommend this spot for a super tasty dish.
A wonderful welcome to New Orleans! I had the Pineapple Tofu for entree and the pralines for dessert. We'll be back!
Lots of drink options, alcoholic and non. Made a refreshing stop.
Yum
Fabulous vegetarian food
Outdoor, shaded seating with attentive service and tasty vegan fare. Excellent!
The perfect place for vegetarian, vegan & gluten free food

We ate here multiple times in just a 4-day visit to the city. It has great options for vegan and vegetarian as well as meat choices. We were able to have unique and very flavorful veg food each time. They also have great beer and wine choices.
Of course New Orleans is all about the food, drinks and experience. I'm vegetarian ..so at this restaurant you can find great vegetarian  meals. Delicious. Good drinks. Friendly server.
Good vegetarian options with adequate quantity. Uttapam roll could have done with a little more salt.
Looking for a quick bite in an informal place? Look no further. Delicious food.

As described very eclectic, adored my sweet potato biscuits and gravy. My partner got Indian food, all vegetarian. We sat outside and an enjoyed fancy mixology drinks . Wish I would have taken a picture !!

Even though the food was delicious and inventive, we felt cheated. The service was really bad. People were not nice and not professional. The dessert menu was never presented to us once we finished our meal. The waiter was rude when we asked some advice. It was also very expensive.
Good food but the service was appalling. And we come from France, so we know about bad service, this was a lot worse.
Delicious vegan options!
Great vegan choices and beautiful ambiance
The only thing going for it is the setting. Very slow on process and light on quantity for the price.
Food was decent if a bit overpriced. Maybe my server was having a bad day, but he was  bristly and unfriendly.
Phenomenal place; hidden in an alley. Great food and unique options! Definitely recommended, especially if you’re a vegetarian or a vegan.
Delicious! This place is great, especially for people with dietary restrictions such as Celiac or food allergies.

Green Goddess had great vegan options and careful attention to details. The staff seemed a little out of it, but that didn't seem to stop them from being prompt and observed every special request. The food was thoughtfully arranged, carefully prepared and totally tasty. The drinks were also a refreshing change from the cloying norm of NOLA. The portions were reasonable and the price was appropriate for the area. The coconut bananas foster was incredible. I'd recommend this pace for anyone with food allergies or dietary restrictions or just someone looking for a great restaurant with something lighter than the conventional fare in the French Quarter.
Really good food and service!
Tiny little place with great vegetarian food. Gets crowded fast. Good service. Unique menu items. Must eat here for vegetarians.
The best meal I have ever eaten thus far in my life.

Just yum! This place is great, vegan friendly and overall such great food. Awesome atmosphere, I ate outside at a table. I could have eaten one of everything on the menu it all looked that good. Must visit!
One of the best restaurants with vegan, Gf, and vegetarian food options in New Orleans. The food was amazing and they had great service!
The Tofu Poboy is fantastic and so is the Rolled Uttappam.. great vegetarian and other choices..
They need more outdoor umbrellas
Amazing food! Great vegan / vegetarian options.... The wait is not too bad, but depending on your server you could be there for a while.
Quaint place, great duck sauage. I eat here every time I'm in town.

Food was good and great to be outdoors. Would have liked to be placed closer to main area. I was dining alone. They were busy and put up another table but it was so far away from other diners that I felt like a punished child. Asked if table could be put closer but was told not possible because of a doorway. Spoiled an otherwise pleasant meal. A few passersby commented on this apparent isolation. I appreciate that they seated me and recognize that I was alone but other solo diners noted at tables for 4.

Just left the place. Nice location and nice staff except the guy name randy as far as I remember. It’s really too pricy and I kept telling him r u for real giving this price for locals for 3 small corn and tiny lattes. Was charged 8.88 for these stuff. Take care of your locals since after the jazz fest u will have locals to come. Btw I did mention to him the list of local places who provide the discount for locals and he barley was listening and trying to prove the point. Locals means noting to them
The food here was awesome!  The menu was very unique!
Awesome place for vegetarians/vegans. Only small gripe is that they ran out of the good wine and we had to drink something else... Otherwise, loved it!

The food was delicious and it's location is quite cute. It's located in a walkway that is inaccessible to vehicles with lots of plants. Lots of vegetarian options, though I believe you can still get meat there. It was pretty much the only veggie restaurant around. The salad was delicious and they make tofu actually taste good! It was a short walk from our hotel. The service was good. Very hipster,  but not uncomfortably so.
The freaked salad alone is worth the trip.
Great staff, great atmosphere and great food! We visited this restaurant multiple times during our stay.

Great food , the Swedish meatloaf was so delish (yum) , they have good vegetarian selections as well & soup of the day was curry (so good) The restaurant lies in a small alley hiding from the busy streets , perfect location to sit outside without being bothered by the endless movement in this neighborhood..
Very good food. Off beat, intimate space. Vegan, vegetarian, and meat options. Good service also
Nice to see some healthy options after all the heavy food in New Orleans, all of it was delicious and the service was brilliant and our waiter gave us loads of information.
Amazing food and staff, sit in next to the kitchen for the music
Awesome!
Warm and cozy.
Great vegetarian options!
Incredibly underwhelming food. Very expensive for what it is. Good service and nice atmosphere though.

Tasty food and fast service. We got the vegi Cuban luau, barratta roll and tofu poboy, and for app we got the hummas beet. The place was pretty small but I guess that's part of the experience. For some odd reason they had already added the tip at 22%, which makes no sense since we weren't even a large party and the menu was pretty pricy.
Food was fantastic!
Wonderful food!  The Indian crepe was wonderful and loved their potatoe appetizer!  Must visit.

Pretentious food.... Can't actually  differentiate between a masala dosa and an utthapa. Major disappointment. Staff was friendly and service was excellent... Food a bit pricey and honestly not worth the hype created around it. Loved the ambience though and it's an amazing place for a first date too... it has an amazing feel to it....
Love the food. But you gotta eat out.
Great little place with delicious vegetarian and meat options. Potions sizes are value for the money. Service was friendly and fast. Definitely recommend!
Great food (veg and vegan options available), outdoor seating on charming side street
Loved this place! Cool laid back vibe and delicious food. Also loved the chicory coffee here
Vegan Po Boys!

Great place to grab vegetarian/ vegan food in the French Quarter. (They are not exclusively vegetarian/vegan; just that they offer more than 1 option for vegetarians). They don't accept reservations and there is a line up but the food is worth the wait.  The restaurant is in an alleyway and the tables are all outside. The street lights, neighboring stores add to the eclectic ambience.
Got the vegan po boy and it was incredible.
Red lentil wrap is a delicious vegan option.
great vegetarian restaurant hidden in an alley
Layers upon layers of flavors! The menu has Vegetarian/Vegan options. Outdoor sitting on the alley at night is quite nice.

Beautiful outdoors settintg, excellent food, with great drinks, and friendly staff. The food has much flavor, is delicious, and there's a lot of options for vegetarians and vegans. The drinks are well made and quite generous.
Best meal I've had in NOLA  lovely quite spot. Will be back
Best of the best. The menu is creative and seasonned.
Amazing menu and even better food! Vegan friendly! Located in the adorable Exchange alley.
Excellent menu, beautiful outdoor seating, and friendly staff.
Great little place with interesting food.
Great biscuits and cocktails, but the service is not. Ordered a beer and never got it.  Too busy putting umbrellas away.

Vegan food in New Orleans is rare, so to find a place that didn't just have something that I could eat, but that had choices, we couldnt pass it up!  The food was really good (I had a lemongrass tofu po boy), and sitting outside in a cute little artsy alley was a bit surreal considering how close it was to Bourbon Street! (just don't order the naked mary cocktail!  it tasted like a tomato vodka pasta sauce...great as a sauce, not as a drink!)

Seriously, if you’re vegan is hard to find a good restaurant in the city. Go for this place. Is very charming and is kinda hidden in a an alleyway. You won’t be disappointed. Their drinks are amazing as well.
Amazing vegan and vegetarian food. Absolutely love every bite, every time I eat here!
Uttapam roll is good. It's fusion of south indian uttapam
This is a great breakfast/brunch place.  It is especially great if you are a vegetarian.  You will be sitting outside, so keep that in mind.  The sweet potato biscuits were great.
Ordered the chimichurri mushroom dish. Amazing flavors well balanced with the plantain cake. Wonderful vegetarian place

By far one of my favorite places to eat in New Orleans. Fabulous atmosphere, good service, and excellent food, especially for vegans and vegetarians. Killer vegan bloody mary for brunch. Highly recommended!

I was pretty disappoined by this place. I wanted to have salad for dinner and this place looked right. However their salad meals are very basic and you still have to pay extra to add some cheese, chicken or shrimp to make it a decent meal and It ended up costing me $23 for eating in an alley. For that much money i could have had a much better salad in a nicer atmosphere

The food was great but they have no idea how to split checks or understand what customer service is! Big parties be warned they will ask you to split the one check they give you yourself and that doing anything to help you is not their policy!
Great food with good enough service. Had beet hummus, Swedish meatloaf, Patatas bravas. Bourbon in bloom and rose garden libations. Give the place a shot.

Would love to tell you how good this place is but unfortunately they wouldn't let me place a to go order until they didn't have a wait for table service. There were three parties waiting for a table, but there were also three free tables. I think they were just short on servers because the woman seemed like she really didn't want to deal with my questions. But that kinda seems like the perfect time for to go orders ¯_(ツ)_/¯

When I got there the girl was super over bearing talking to me like I wasn't supposed to be there it was my first time there , I didn't know that their lunch hour was over .they were rude af basically so I left.
Beautiful courtyard. Unique food and cocktails, good vegeterain and vegan selections

Had this salad there, on a hot saturday afternoon. The salad was good, I mean, not your usual boring salad. And the service was friendly too. A good place where to have a quick snack. Prices range from 7$ to about 15$, FYI.
Good vegan poboys. Very cozy. Literally a nook in the wall. Somewhat hard to spot in a car.
I really like the food and sitting outside. Has a few good vegetarian options.
Great food. Lacks atmosphere.
Mmmmm great lil spot in the FQ.
An excellent place for a quick brunch. The citric salad, beet humus were great for starters.
Delicious, fresh food with lots of vegetarian, gluten free options. Also situated in a beautiful courtyard.
Needs more vegan options.
Several vegetarian/vegan/gluten free options that seem delicious. Since we are in NOLA, there were also beef, duck, and shell fish options. Reasonably priced. Excellent food.
Salad!!! And nice, quiet outdoor seating.
Delicious and healthy, perfect combo
Great food in an interesting atmosphere.

Must eat Restaurant when in New Orleans. NOTE: Outside seating only. Food is 5 out of 5 hands down. Service maybe 4 out of 5, because we arrived right at Dinner time, 6pm. I ordered the Charcuterie and Red Eye Pork and oh boy they were outstanding. Each item on the plates is packed with flavors and the pork was cooked to perfection. I don't think I have ever had cooked Kale taste so good.
Fun. Casual. Outdoor seating.
Unique food lovingly prepared. Really something different. May be your only chance to see a vegetable in NO. Only outdoor seating. Good drinks. Quirky hours, so check before walking over.
A bit pricey. Decent vegetarian options.
Fresh and original fare, good prices when considering the locations.  Staff was friendly and prompt.
Truly inventive menu... and everything's absolutely amazing! The beet hummus and patatas bravas are to die for. This is a must if you're in town.

Lot more options for veg and Vegan, not all heavy stodgy meals as I've become accustomed to expect. Eaten here twice during visit and both times Had the Indian dosa style dish. Did find it nourishing and filling.
Great vegan poboy

Visiting New Orleans for a few days you need to find this nice restaurant hidden in a French Quarter alley. The service is quick, menu is simple and they have excellent appetizers. The salads are fresh, vegetables and seafood were great. Their signature green goddess dressing is a delicious thing to try.
Some of the best food we came across in New Orleans!
Stellar greens, delicious cocktails, the service  is the best! Return visit guaranteed!

The wait staff here is cooler than you. They listened to Mac DeMarco before you and they can wear German flight suits to work. Once you accept that, you can enjoy this place much more. It's tucked into a beautiful alley in the French Quarter. They have the best vegetarian food in the whole city
Fantastic food!!!
Good place to try out a menu with wide influence of cuisines. Recommended to go at night preferably with a group of friends to enjoy great conversations, the natural breeze and the yummy food.
Always delicious, friendly and fresh. This little gem never disappoints.
Food was good, but a little pricey.  I had the Swedish meatloaf Po boy and it was too sweet, not what I was looking for.
A wonderful little restaurant! The service was quick and courteous. The food was delicious and the cocktails were inventive.
Dinner was a tough decision with all the fresh menu options. Also good to stop for wine and cheese.
This a gem in the rough of the French Quarter! Awesome Veg/Vegan place to eat! You might have to wait for a table at lunch time but it is well worth it!
Fantastic food and a great song to go with it.
Very cozy place on a pedestrian small st. Good was great
Been here many times. Never disappointed. Great place if you are looking for some vegetarian options.
Good food service could be improved.
Good food. Great vegetarian options.
Really nice to-go salads in a city focused on meats and seafoods. Great place to visit if you're in town for a conference!

This is probably my favorite restaraunt ever.  I make a point to visit everytime I am in New Orleans. I appreciate how playful the chefs are and am always surprised by the deliciously unexpected combinations found here.  The cheese plate is one of the best in the city, well worth the $22.  Sadly, for Neil Gaiman blog followers, as of 12/30/16, the staff no longer knew what the "Mezze of Destruction " is. =(
Good salads
Great location. Good food, but not fantastic. Standard spreads.
Had apps and cocktails while sitting outside under the string of lights - incredibly tasty!
